 English translations of classical Chinese, Mandarin, and French texts in Chinese philosophy and culture. This innovative work of comparative philosophy not only presents a systematic and comprehensive interpretation of Wang's thought but also shows its relevance to contemporary discussions in the philosophy of ecology.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aHumanism. 0aNeo-Confucianism. 0aPhilosophy of nature. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Philosophy. 4aEnvironmental Studies : Environmental Studies. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Environment and Religion. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Religion. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Eastern / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2017z978311149102840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143846455840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438464558423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438464558/original  a978-3-11-149102-8  SUNY Press eBook Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles